# 18. ふたりの呪い

Kanade: Yuki...
Mizuki: Thank goodness! We found you!
???: Why?
???: Miku, did you bring them here?
Miku: .....
???: Why did you come back?
???: I told you to leave me alone.
Kanade: I came because I want you to listen to my song.
???: Your song?
Kanade: You said before that my music wasn't enough.
Kanade: So I made another song. One that will be able to save you this time.
???: .....
???: I don't need it anymore.
Kanade: Yuki.
???: Just leave me alone.
???: Miku, get them out of here.
Miku: .....
???: Miku, did you hear me? Hurry up and get rid of these two.
Miku: Listen to it.
???: Huh?
Miku: Listen...to her song.
???: Not you too... Why?
Kanade: Please, Yuki.
???: Go away! I just want to be left alone so I can disappear!
???: I don't want your help!
Kanade: !!
Mizuki: K, your phone!
???: Now get out...
???: Stop barging in here when you don't know a single thing about me!
Kanade: I do know.
Kanade: You said it yourself, Yuki. You accused us all of wanting to disappear.
Kanade: You were right. I want to disappear so badly I don't know what to do.
Kanade: All because my music caused the person I care for most to suffer.
???: You what?
Kanade: My dad used to be a songwriter.
Kanade: He worked so hard, always hoping that his music would bring people happiness.
Kanade: I wanted to be like him, so I started writing songs myself.
Kanade: But the songs I wrote only pushed my dad into a corner.
Mizuki: Your songs...did that?
Kanade: Yeah. He had suffered for so long because the songs he made were old and nobody wanted them.
Kanade: But I kept making him listen to my music, not realizing he was forcing himself to smile as he did.
Kanade: That just made things worse. It forced him to think about the fact he wasn't able to write music like mine.
Kanade: He lost confidence in himself and ended up collapsing from the pressure. And now he can't make music anymore.
Mizuki: That's terrible. But is it really your fault, Kanade?
Kanade: .....
Kanade: Yes, it's my fault. I'm the one who hurt him. I took away the music he loved so much, and his future with it.
Kanade: I started wanting to disappear so badly it hurt.
Kanade: But my dad told me that I had to keep creating music. That's...
Kanade: That's the only thing keeping me going. I have to keep writing music that can save others.
Kanade: Songs that can rescue them no matter how hopeless they feel. So even though I just want to disappear, I have to keep composing.
???: .....
Kanade: So... I understand how you feel, Yuki.
Kanade: Though our situations might be a little different.
???: I...see.
???: You've been cursed by your own father, K.
Kanade: .....
???: A curse you can never be free of. How sad.
???: But I don't give a damn about your curse, so don't get me involved in your problems.
???: You're only trying to save me because you want to help yourself. A vain, desperate struggle.
???: All that will do is make us both suffer.
???: After all, the truth is you just want to disappear.
Kanade: .....
Kanade: That may be true, but still...
Miku: Maybe those shared feelings are why your song was the only thing able to get through.
Miku: Even if it wasn't enough...it still reached her.
Kanade: I learned that the song I wrote reached you, Yuki.
Kanade: That's why I want to save you with my music. As long as there is still a chance, I will save you.
Kanade: Even if this is a curse.
